<HEADER>
A8472 &Cx1f; tab-z
r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NATO-FRIEND-NOT-FIEND     04-22 1348
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NATO-FRIEND-NOT-FIEND-600&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`THANK YOU, NATTO!': NATO ACQUITTED IN REFUGEE CAMPS  
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (EDITORS: Timely for NATO's 50th birthday this weekend!)   (This excellent ``separate buy'' article _ IDEAL FOR THIS WEEKEND'S
COVERAGE OF NATO'S 50TH ANNIVERSARY _ is from The Independent
newspaper in London.)  
  
 (EDITORS: We regret that this material is NOT available to clients
in Canada EXCEPT to The Hamilton (Ontario) Spectator.)  
  
 (To publish this article, it must be purchased from the New York
Times Syndicate's sales representative DEBRA WEYDERT at
732-390-4480, or fax her at 732-390-4697. If unable to reach Ms.
Weydert, please call 800-444-0267, or fax us at 816-822-1444.)  
  
 (ATTN. EDITORS: FOR THOSE NEEDING A SHORTER VERSION, THIS ARTICLE
CAN STAND IN 600 WORDS. FULL UNCUT VERSION IS 1,025 WORDS.)  
  
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted twice _ into the
``a'' domestic/general news and ``k'' commentary news files.)  
  
 By RICHARD LLOYD PARRY  
 c.1999 The Independent, London  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SKOPJE, MACEDONIA _ NATO has acquitted itself with honor. Not
through its military efforts or in the political arena _ but
through the alliance's outstanding response to the aid crisis.
</P>
