<P>
   BOOKS-SKUBE _ A first-time author on tour is anxious about
reviews, anxious about sales, anxious about making a good
impression. In Michael Isikoff's case, there was anxiety of another
kind as well. At Chapter 11, while he was signing copies of
``Uncovering Clinton,'' a display case promoting George
Stephanopoulos' ``All Too Human'' flanked him, and one could hardly
notice Isikoff's book without noticing the other. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
