   BOOKS-HADRIANWALLS _ A review of ``Hadrian's Walls'' by Robert
Draper. (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: EMBARGOED UNTIL SUNDAY, APRIL 25
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-KARON _ BLOWING ROCK, N.C. _ Author Jan Karon lives just
as her readers imagine _ in a little pink house in a picturesque
mountain village that is obviously the model for Mitford, the town
she created and which, in turn, made her famous. (White, Cox News
Service). WITH PHOTOS and LAYOUTS
</P>
<P>
   EDs: EMBARGOED UNTIL SUNDAY, APRIL 25
</P>
<P>
   BOOKNOTES _ If Bridget Jones is the voice of the modern British
woman, Nick Hornby is the male counterpart. Hornby's books, ``High
Fidelity'' and ``About a Boy'' have become best sellers and are
headed for the big screen. John Cusack is starring in ``High
Fidelity'' and Robert DeNiro has bought rights to ``About a Boy.''
We talk to Hornby on the eve of his Atlanta visit on Friday; Also,
``Cold Sassy Tree,'' the novel by the late Atlanta author Olive Ann
Burns, is scheduled to be done as an opera by Carlisle Floyd for
the Houston Grand Opera Co. (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MANNING-DEPRESSION _ PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Martha Manning was a
clinical psychologist, counseling patients by day and teetering on
the brink of suicide at night. She underwent electric shock
treatment, and has written a book about her experience. (Gelormine,
Palm Beach Post Daily News) MOVED SUNDAY.
</P>
