</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PROMOTION-DATA-$ADV25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With PROMOTION. For release Sunday, April 25.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DELAYED PROMOTIONS IN CHICAGO PUBLIC SCHOOLS
</P>
<P>
   Combined totals for 3rd, 6th and 8th grades
</P>
<P>
   Enrolled in May 1998 ............. 99,527 (100 percent)
</P>
<P>
   Promoted in June 1998 .......... 74,168 (74.5 percent)
</P>
<P>
   Promoted in August 1998 ....... 13,207 (13.2 percent)
</P>
<P>
   Promoted in January 1999 ....... 4,584 (4.6 percent)
</P>
<P>
   Not Promoted by April 1999 ..... 7,568 (7.7 percent)
</P>
<P>
   Source: Chicago public schools.
</P>
<P>
   Note: Eligibility for promotions can be based on grades, tests
and attendance, meeting special-education or bilingual-education
goals, or, in rare cases, waivers.
</P>
<P>
   CHICAGO'S 'CHILDREN FIRST' PROMOTION STANDARDS FOR GRADES 3, 6
AND 8
</P>
<P>
   Students must meet these three criteria:
</P>
<P>
   1. Passing grade in reading and mathematics, or scores at or
above grade
</P>
<P>
   level on those sections of the Iowa Tests of Basic Skills.
</P>
<P>
   2. No more than 20 days of unexcused absence.
</P>
<P>
   3. Minimum score in reading and mathematics on Iowa Tests of
Basic Skills:
</P>
<P>
   _ Grade 3: One year below grade level.
</P>
<P>
   _ Grade 6: One and a half years below grade level.
</P>
<P>
   _ Grade 8: One and a half years below grade level.
</P>
<P>
   ALTERNATIVES:
</P>
<P>
   Separate criteria for students in bilingual education programs.
</P>
<P>
   Criteria may be modified on an individual basis for students
receiving
</P>
<P>
   special education services.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Parent Guide to the Chicago Public Schools Promotion
Policy
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
