   &UR; CRASH COURSE &LR;  _ Damaged combat aircraft should soon stand a
better chance of making it back to base, thanks to a novel neural
network that has just passed its first major test. The software,
developed by NASA, is designed to assess flight data during an
emergency and work out the best way to maintain a normal flight
when control surfaces are damaged or malfunctioning. By Duncan
