<P>
   CALIFORNIA-BOXER-GUNS. In the wake of the Colorado high school
killings, Sen. Barbara Boxer again is pressing for a change in the
1994 Crime Bill. She would like to ease the financial burden on
local communities when it comes to paying for police officer in
schools. In a letter first sent to Attorney General Janet Reno last
summer, Boxer asked for the lifting of a federal requirement that
communities must pay 25 percent of the overall cost. (250 words.)
By Mark Stricherz
</P>
