   COLORADO-SHOOTING-CONGRESS. Colorado lawmakers have always tried
to make their Capitol Hill offices feel like home, cluttering the
walls with Broncos posters, paintings of the Rockies and
Indian-print rugs. In the wake of Tuesday's shootings in Littleton,
there was no need to proclaim the Colorado connection. The state's
pain could be felt here too. (500 words.) By Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO-SPANISH-PEAKS. U.S. Rep. Scott McInnis, R-Colo.,
Thursday asked a House committee to fast-track a bill that would
give the government's strictest level of environmental protection
to 18,000 acres of forest around the Spanish Peaks. (200 words.) By
Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
