interstate garbage, two former governors now in the U.S. Senate
introduced legislation Thursday that would give states a greater
role in determining who gets to use their landfills. (400 words.)
By C.J. Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   INDIANA-VISCLOSKY-WATER - U.S. Rep. Pete Visclosky today
introduced a bill that calls for the establishment of a federal
trust fund to clean polluted waters. (400 words.) By C.J.
Karamargin
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-DRUG-ALLEN. Drug makers and U.S. Rep. Tom Allen, D-Maine,
fired new salvos this week in their high-stakes battle over whether
the federal government should regulate how much old people pay for
prescription drugs. The drug makers' trade group released a study
on Monday that appears to debunk Democratic lawmakers' claims that
the industry gouges older Americans with unfair prices. And
Thursday, lawmakers responded with a critique of the new study. At
stake is Allen's ``Prescription Drug Fairness Act,'' a high-profile
bill that would force drug makers to charge neighborhood pharmacies
the same prices they give their bulk customers. (600 words.) By
Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   NEVADA-NUKE-WASTE. Efforts to store the nation's high-level
