<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release FRIDAY AMs, April 23, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BALKANS &LR;   &UR; CONFLICT (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Washington) _ Senior Russian official says Slobodan
Milosevic is prepared to permit the United Nations to send an
``international presence'' into Kosovo if NATO forces stop
pummeling his country. By Bob Hohler. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HONKONG-DISSIDENTS (Hong Kong) _ Democracy activists criticize
Hong Kong for barring entry to 11 Chinese dissidents, accusing the
local government of undermining Hong Kong's autonomy from mainland
China. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GUNS-MCCARTHY (Washington) _ A nurse turned congresswoman, whose
her bid for Congress was ignited by the crackle of gunfire, says
the Capitol Hill calculus that has consigned gun-control bills to
legislative limbo has been rewritten by the Colorado school
shootings. By Thomas Farragher. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTING (Littleton, Colo. ) _ The outcasts who massacred their
classmates before killing themselves intended to blow up the
school, authorities say after discovering two large propane tanks
wired with explosives. By Mitchell Zuckoff. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   MISSING-LINK (Undated) _ Remains of a 2 1/2 million-year-old
creature found in Ethiopa may be the immediate predecessor of
humans, researchers say. The creature, something halfway between
the famed ``Lucy'' and true pre-humans, ate meat. By David L.
Chandler. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BANKBOS-GIFFORD (Boston) _ BankBoston shareholders speculate
that chief executive Chad Gifford might opt not to assume the reins
of the new company his bank will form with Fleet, despite an
extraordinary contract. By Lynnley Browning. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-SUIT (Undted) _ Software firm settles a class-action lawsuit
over the Y2K bug. Suit was filed after the company allegedly
refused to update its programs to prevent problems in the new
millennium. By Ross Kerber. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-TIGERS (Detroit) _ Tigers 1, Red Sox 0. By Gordon
Edes.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS-CANES (Greensboro, N.C.) _ By Nancy Marrapese.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS-GILL (Greensboro, N.C.) _ Hal Gill has become a key
component of the Boston defense, mainly because of his height (6
feet 7) and weight (240 pounds). It also helps being an agile block
of granite willing to work at getting better. By Kevin Paul Dupont.
900 words.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-CELTICS-HAWKS (Atlanta) By Michael Vega.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BOWES (Durham, N.H.) _ UNH football coach Bill Bowes calls
it quits after 27 years leading the Wildcats. By Allen Lessels. 800
words.
</P>
