<P>
   &UR; BALKANS &LR;   &UR; CONFLICT (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA (Washington) _ Senior Russian official says Slobodan
Milosevic is prepared to permit the United Nations to send an
``international presence'' into Kosovo if NATO forces stop
pummeling his country. By Bob Hohler. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HONKONG-DISSIDENTS (Hong Kong) _ Democracy activists criticize
Hong Kong for barring entry to 11 Chinese dissidents, accusing the
local government of undermining Hong Kong's autonomy from mainland
China. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
