<P>
   PHOTO EDITORS: We would like to call attention to the following
photos moved today, Thursday, April 22, 1998, with stories on the
school shooting in Littleton, Colo., as well as the ongoing refugee
crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   Photo clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) LITTLETON, Colo. -- April 22, 1999 --
COLO-SCHOOL-SHOOTING-2, 4-22 -- The car parked in the lot outside
Columbine High School, belonging to Rachel Scott who was killed in
Tuesday's shooting rampage, has become a makeshift memorial two
days after the incident. The two outcasts who massacred their
classmates before killing themselves on Tuesday intended to blow up
the school, authorities said after discovering two large propane
bombs hidden in the school's kitchen. (Andrea Mohin/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) MORINA, Albania -- April 22, 1999 -- KOSOVO-REFUGEES-1,
4-22 -- An Albanian soldier and police officer stand at a border
crossing as a group of ethnic Albanian refugees fleeing Kosovo head
to cross it on Thursday. Hundreds of refugees from Kosovo flowed
into northeastern Albania Thursday, telling of their traumatic trek
during which they were beaten and robbed by Serb police. (Edward
Keating/New York Times Photo)
</P>
