<SLUG> BC-PIPPEN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PIPPEN HIT WITH DWI CHARGE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Filed on both sports and national news wires.) 
 
By S.K. BARDWELL 
c. 1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Houston Rockets star Scottie Pippen was arrested and
charged with driving while intoxicated early Thursday, hours after
after turning in one of the worst performances of his career with
the Rockets.
</P>
<P>
   Houston police officer Ross McCammon said he pulled Pippen's
Mercedes over at 1:20 a.m. after seeing his car drive south in the
northbound lanes of a major downtown Houston street.
</P>
<P>
   After talking with Pippen, McCammon suspected him to be
intoxicated, and called a member of the DWI Task Force to the
scene, said HPD spokesman John Cannon.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen failed a field sobriety test and was arrested. He was
taken to the downtown police station, where authorities said he was
videotaped and refused a Breathalyzer test.
</P>
<P>
   Although Pippen, 33, was alone in his Mercedes, Houston Police
Department spokesman Robert Hurst said Pippen's brother was in a
car with friends who pulled over when they saw Pippen being
stopped.
</P>
<P>
   Hurst said after police made sure Pippen's brother was sober and
legally licensed, he was allowed to drive Pippen's car away, rather
than having it towed and impounded.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was charged with misdemeanor DWI and bail set at $500. He
was released from the city jail just before 7 a.m. after posting
bond, police said. He is scheduled for an initial court appearance
on April 29.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was not intoxicated when arrested after the game last night,
and I'm confident the evidence will support me in the end,'' Pippen
said in a statement released through the Rockets' media office late
Thursday. ``I have no further comment and am going to let my
attorneys handle this matter in the appropriate way.''
</P>
<P>
   Houston criminal defense lawyer Rusty Hardin said he spoke with
Pippen after his release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He and the people who were with him adamantly deny that he was
intoxicated,'' Hardin said.
</P>
<P>
   Hardin said he knows little about the case and declined to say
who was with Pippen or where he was before he was arrested
downtown.
</P>
<P>
   However, patrons of The Jones Bar downtown said Pippen was there
after the game Wednesday, along with Charles Barkley and Matt
Maloney.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen left town Thursday with his team for a West Coast road
trip. The Rockets play the Los Angeles Clippers Friday and the
Phoenix Suns on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday night, the Rockets lost 109-95 to the Dallas Mavericks
in Compaq Center, with Pippen contributing only four points, making
just two of his eight shots in 31 minutes of play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know what happened. I'm with him 110 percent,'' Barkley said
Thursday. ``If everybody's kids grew up to be as successful as
Scottie Pippen, the world would be a better place.''
</P>
<P>
   Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich said: ``I don't think it's
appropriate for us to comment. We don't have the details.
Commenting on those things is unfair.
</P>
<P>
   ``People did that to me and assumed things. It's not fair. I'm
not going to do that to anybody,'' Tomjanovich said, referring to
his own arrest for DWI in West University Place in the summer of
1994.
</P>
<P>
   The charges against Tomjanovich, who also was represented by
Hardin, were dismissed a few days after being filed, when
prosecutors said they had insufficient evidence.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was arrested in Chicago in January 1994 after a police
officer checking on Pippen's illegally parked car noticed a loaded
.380-caliber semiautomatic handgun in the car. The charge was later
dismissed when a judge ruled the officer had no probable cause to
look in the car.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was charged with misdemeanor domestic battery in May
1995, after being accused of grabbing his fiancee, Yvette Deleone,
and shoving her. The case was dismissed when Deleone declined to
testify.
</P>
<P>
   XXXXX END OF STORY
</P>
</TEXT>
