<HEADLINE>
VAN GUNDY STILL STANDING, BUT ON UNSTABLE GROUND
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: See also BKN-HORNETS-SILAS)  
(DW) 
 By SELENA ROBERTS   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Jeff Van Gundy was working a roll of ankle tape in
his hand. He had walked down a gray hallway inside Madison Square
Garden, flipping the roll against the wall and catching it as he
made his way to an interview room.
</P>
<P>
   As he sat down, he appeared weary and unshaven. Although on
