<HEADER>
A9691 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BOOKTAB-BIOGRAPHIES25     04-22 0982
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOOKTAB-BIOGRAPHIES25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    List of new biographies
 &HT;    EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, April 25.
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The First Partner _ Hillary Rodham Clinton. By Joyce Milton.
Morrow. $26. Milton offers a detailed chronicle of the life of the
much-discussed first lady and possible U.S. Senate candidate. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Jonathan Swift. By Victoria Glendinning. Holt. $35. Following
her engaging portrait of Rebecca West, Glendinning tackles the life
of the 18th-century satirist. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Madeleine Albright: A Twentieth-Century Odyssey. By Michael
Dobbs. Holt. $27.50. The first female secretary of state is
profiled by Washington Post reporter Dobbs. (May)
</P>
<P>
   1185 Park Avenue: A Memoir. By Anne Roiphe. Free Press. $25. The
acclaimed novelist revisits her childhood and her parents' troubled
marriage. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Twilight of the Wagners. By
</P>
<P>
   Gottfried Wagner. Picador USA. $26. In this controversial
memoir, Richard Wagner's great-grandson unveils his family's legacy
of anti-Semitism and their intimate relationship with Hitler. (May)
</P>
<P>
   My Father's Gun. By Brian McDonald. Dutton. $24.95. A family
memoir of life with a grandfather, father and older brother who
were Irish-American cops in New York City. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Harp Song for a Radical: The Life and Times of Eugene Victor
Debs. By Marguerite Young. Knopf. $35. A monumental biography of
the founder of the International Workers of the World and the
American Socialist Party. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Caravaggio: A Life. By Helen Langdon. Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux.
$30. A portrait of the artist as a painter of transcendental
brilliance and a hard-living genius fascinated with the fringes of
17th-century Roman society. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Groovin' High: The Life of Dizzy Gillespie. By Alyn Shipton.
Oxford. $30. The first full biography of the jazz great since his
death in 1993. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Pushkin. By Elaine Feinstein. Ecco Press. $29.95. The
paradoxical life of the father of Russian literature is explored in
this biography, published to coincide with the bicentennial of his
birth. (May)
</P>
<P>
   Lorca: A Dream of Life. By Leslie Stainton. Farrar, Straus &AMP;
Giroux. $35. Using newly discovered archival material, Stainton
draws a vivid picture of Spain's greatest modern poet. (June)
</P>
<P>
   The View From Alger's Window. By Tony Hiss. Knopf. $24. Hiss
provides a new perspective on his father's life and relates his own
experience as a young boy during his father's trial for perjury in
a controversial espionage case. (June)
</P>
<P>
   Moab Is My Washpot. By Stephen Fry. Random House. $24. Fry is a
rare mix: talented actor and accomplished author. In this memoir,
he revisits his school days with his usual wit and charm. (June)
</P>
<P>
   Life Is Just What You Make It. By Donny Osmond and Patricia
Romanowski. Hyperion. $22.95. The toothy Mormon heartthrob shares
the story of his life and career. (June)
</P>
<P>
   Love Is Where It Falls: An Account of a Passionate Friendship.
By Simon Callow. Fromm International. $23. Callow recounts his
unusual relationship with flamboyant theatrical agent Margaret
Ramsay. The pair met in 1980 and carried on an intensely emotional
affair of the heart despite an age difference of nearly 40 years
and the fact that Callow was involved in a homosexual relationship.
(June)
</P>
<P>
   Undressed: The Life and Times of Gianni Versace. By Christopher
Mason. Little, Brown. $25. Mason delves into the complex world of
the late fashion designer, from his early years in Reggio di
Calabrio, Italy, to his murder by Andrew Cunanan in front of his
palatial Miami home. (July)
</P>
<P>
   Denmark Vesey: The Buried History of America's Largest Slave
Rebellion. By David Robertson. Knopf. $23. Robertson profiles the
leader on a failed early 19th-century slave revolt that ended with
Vesey and five co-conspirators being hanged on July 22, 1822,
outside Charleston, S.C. (July)
</P>
<P>
   George Eliot: The Last Victorian. By Kathryn Hughes. Farrar,
Straus &AMP; Giroux. $30. Hughes investigates the personal dramas that
shaped Eliot's life and work, along with her social and
intellectual context. (July)
</P>
<P>
   Don Imus. By Kathleen Tracy and Rick Joyce. Carroll &AMP; Graf. $25.
Tracing the rise of the irascible radio jock. (August)
</P>
<P>
   Edward Albee: A Singular Journey. By Mel Gussow. Simon &AMP;
Schuster. $30. Gussow takes readers through the lauded playwright's
rocky life and offers insight into his lauded dramatic work.
(August)
</P>
<P>
   The Secret Life of Dr. Laura Schlessinger. By Vickie Bane. St.
Martin's. Price TBA. Are there any more skeletons in the closet of
the popular radio host and reluctant pin-up? Do we really want to
know? (August)
</P>
<P>
   The Messenger: The Rise and Fall of Elijah Muhammad. By Karl
Evanzz. Pantheon. $27.50. Evanzz had access to previously
unreleased FBI files and the cooperation of some of Muhammad's
children and associates in compiling this biography of the
co-founder of the Nation of Islam. (August)
</P>
<P>
   Andy Kaufman Revealed! By Bob Zmuda. Little, Brown. $24. Close
friend and producer Zmuda shares his memories of the influential
comedian in anticipation of the fall release of the Kaufman biopic
starring Jim Carrey. (August)
</P>
<P>
   Naked Tango: The Life and Fictions of Manuel Puig. By Suzanne
Jill Levine. Farrar, Straus &AMP; Giroux. $27.50. The colorful life of
the Argentine author of ``Kiss of the Spider Woman,'' written by
his principal English translator. (August)
</P>
<P>
   T.S. Eliot: An Imperfect Life. By Lyndall Gordon. Norton. $35.
This volume draws together Gordon's previous biographical work on
Eliot, unavailable in recent years, and new material drawn from
recently discovered letters. (August)
</P>
<P>
   Joe DiMaggio: The Hero's Life. By Richard Ben Kramer. Simon &AMP;
Schuster. $27.50. The late, great Yankee is memorialized with the
in-depth biographical treatment. (September)
</P>
<P>
   _ Compiled by Shane Harrison
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
