from their classrooms on Thursday to protest what they called
inadequate pay increases during the past six years. For four of the
past six years, while the cost of living increased 21 percent,
Washington teachers received no salary increases from the state
legislature. Critics of the teachers' proposals have pointed out
that inflation indices overestimate the increase in prices. (Larry
Davis/New York Times Photo)
