<P>
   (NYT34) SEATTLE -- April 22, 1999 -- SEATTLE-WORKOUT, 4-22 --
About 4,000 Seattle teachers and classroom assistants stayed away
from their classrooms on Thursday to protest what they called
inadequate pay increases during the past six years. For four of the
past six years, while the cost of living increased 21 percent,
Washington teachers received no salary increases from the state
legislature. Critics of the teachers' proposals have pointed out
that inflation indices overestimate the increase in prices. (Larry
Davis/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) JERUSALEM -- April 22, 1999 -- ISRAEL-NETANYAHU, 4-22 --
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel in his office last
week. His circle of political allies has shrunk. And the small
clique of advisers, like him, exude a strong air of us against the
world, even though Netanyahu trails his main rival, Ehud Barak, by
only a couple of percentage points. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
