WU-CHINESE-FILMS, 4-22 -- Wu Tianming, seen in the lobby of a New
York hotel recently, is well acquainted with the whims of fortune.
During the 1980s, as an acclaimed director, he headed Xian Film
Studio, the cradle of the New Chinese Cinema, which burst upon the
international scene with the force of a revelation. Less than a
decade later, he was reduced to running a video store in Los
Angeles. Today, Wu, at 60, is once again working as a director in
China. (Ruby Washington/New York Times Photo)
