<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COLO-SCHOOL-VICTIMS-LSTLEDE-WRITETHRU-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PORTRAITS OF 12 WHO DIED IN COLORADO SCHOOL 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: adds last graf to explain additional victim.)  (ART ADV: A photo is being sent to NYT graphic clients.
Non-subscribers can make individual purchase by calling
888-603-1036 or 888-346-9867.) 
(DW) 
 By JAMES BARRON   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CASSIE BERNALL, 17, a junior ... Went from being fascinated by
witchcraft and suicide to being a born-again Christian ... Carried
a Bible to school and wore a bracelet that said, ``What Would Jesus
Do?'' ... Was a fan of ``Braveheart,'' the epic film about 13th
century Scotland that starred Mel Gibson.
</P>
<P>
   STEVEN ROBERT CURNOW, 14, a freshman ... Had played soccer since
he was 5 and had recently become a referee ... Was a ``Star Wars''
fan who memorized the dialogue in the films and amassed a sizable
collection of ``Star Wars'' memorabilia ... Wanted to join the Navy
and become a pilot.
</P>
<P>
   COREY DePOOTER, 17, a junior ... Quit the wrestling team for a
maintenance job at the Racoon Creek Country Club in Littleton so he
could earn money for a fishing boat ... Also liked to go hunting
... Planned to drive to Oklahoma over Easter vacation, but a
snowstorm stopped him at a Holiday Inn in Kansas.
</P>
<P>
   KELLY FLEMING, 16, a junior ... Moved to Littleton from Phoenix
18 months ago ... Wrote dozens of largely autobiographical poems
and short stories ... Was learning to play the guitar ... Had been
looking forward to getting her driver's license and a part-time
job.
</P>
<P>
   MATTHEW KECHTER, 16, a sophomore ... Had hoped to be in the
football team's starting lineup next fall ... Had played a number
of offensive and defensive positions last season and had played on
the ninth-grade squad in 1997-98 ... Was also a weight-lifter ...
Maintained an A average.
</P>
<P>
   DANIEL MAUSER, 15, a sophomore ... A straight-A student who
excelled in math and science, said his father, Tom Mauser ... Ran
cross-country ... Was on the debate team. ... Recently returned
from two-week trip to Paris with his French class.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DANIEL ROHRBOUGH, 15, a freshman ... Shot after running back to
the cafeteria to open a door so other students could flee ... Born
in Littleton but spent a month or two each year at his
grandparents' farm in Colby, Kan. ... Worked after school in his
family's car audio and home theater business in Littleton.
</P>
<P>
   WILLIAM DAVID SANDERS, 48, business teacher and coach ... Known
as Dave ... Married, with four daughters ... Was substituting for a
science teacher on Monday ... Students said he was shot twice as he
tried to lead them to safety ... The women's basketball team posted
a winning record in his first year as coach, 1997-98, after
finishing next-to-last the year before.
</P>
<P>
   RACHEL SCOTT, 17, a senior. Appeared in a student-written school
play, ``Smoke in the Room'' ... Was a mainstay of the debate team,
said Bonnie Baumgart, whose son Nick went to the prom with her last
weekend ... Worked after school at a sandwich shop, earning money
to buy a red Acura her parents had let her borrow ... Enjoyed
photography and a video-production class.
</P>
<P>
   ISAIAH SHOELS, 18, a senior ... Had had heart surgery twice
because of a congenital defect ... Wanted to be a record-company
executive like one of his role models, Master P, the rapper whose
No Limit label turns out hit albums ... Wrestler, football player
and weight-lifter who could bench-press twice his weight.
</P>
<P>
   JOHN TOMLIN, 16, a sophomore ... Moved to Littleton from
Wisconsin in 1995 ... Enjoyed driving a 4-by-4 pickup truck his
father said he bought with money he had saved from an after-school
job in a garden shop ... Lifted weights ... Spent 10 days in Mexico
last year with a church group, building a house for a needy family.
</P>
<P>
   LAUREN TOWNSEND, 18, a senior ... Was the captain of the girls'
volleyball team, coached by her mother ... Was a member of the
National Honor Society ... Planned to attend Colorado State
University in Fort Collins in the fall and wanted to major in
biology ... ``She always knew that no matter what came up, she
could handle it,'' said a friend, Sara Reddon, 17.
</P>
<P>
   One other student, Kyle Velasquez, was killed but information
was not available.
</P>
</TEXT>
