A0002 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  !text! &LR; PASADENA_Whilefor     04-22 0536
</HEADER>
<BODY>
 !text! PASADENA _ While former Galaxy coach Octavio Zambrano asked
for a few days before commenting publicly about his dismissal, team
president Tim Leiweke on Thursday formally announced the hiring of
UCLA head coach Sigi Schmid, arguably the best coach in college
soccer today.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Schmid received a three-year contract, but terms were not
disclosed during a press conference at the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Schmid never had a losing season in 20 years at UCLA. He has won
three NCAA titles, is the fifth-winningest coach in Division I
history (322-63-33, .810) and is a two-time NCAA Coach of the Year.
He also has more former players in Major League Soccer and more
players with the U.S. national team than any coach in the country.
</P>
<P>
   ``His track record speaks for itself,'' Leiweke said. ``He's
really one of the great coaches in the history of the NCAA, and we
felt if the situation ever came where we had to make a move, that
he would be the natural candidate for us.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't bring him in here to ultimately become a failure. We
brought him here because he's been a success every place he's ever
been. And I'm quite confident he'll continue that here.''
</P>
<P>
   Schmid, who was an assistant to U.S. national team coach Bora
Milutinovic during the 1994 World Cup, said he will let assistant
coach Ralph Perez coach the team Saturday against San Jose at the
Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   He said his decision to leave UCLA was the toughest in his
career, and Los Angeles is the only team he considered coaching.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been lucky because I've been able to coach my entire
adult life in this city,'' Schmid said. ``I've spent a lot of years
at UCLA and I would not just leave it for any place.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just think the timing was right and the terms were right.
I've consulted with a lot of people.... I've talked to guys I have
played with in the past all the way to my brother. Everyone has
said this is the right move and the right time, and I'm just happy
to be here and getting to work as soon as possible.''
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy also has seven of his former players, including Cobi
Jones, Paul Caligiuri, Greg Vanney and goalkeeper Kevin Hartman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have complete confidence in this team,'' Schmid said. ``I
think there's a great level of talent here.''
</P>
<P>
   Leiweke said he felt there was a lack of communication between
the players and Zambrano.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had asked Octavio to work on creating a better relationship
and a better style of communications with the players,'' he said.
``It became pretty obvious in the past week that was still an
issue. The players wanted to be coached. They wanted to be
communicated with.
</P>
<P>
   ``They want to be told what they're doing right and what they're
doing wrong and that wasn't happening.''
</P>
<P>
   Some players didn't feel that way.
</P>
<P>
   ``Honestly, it's always been a healthy environment within the
club,'' said Hartman, who acknowledged he was happy with the hiring
of his former coach. ``They (ownership) obviously see things that I
didn't see from that perspective.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know. They're judging the players and I never really
had any major input with that stuff.'' &UR; !dlim!!end! &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
